## [2026-04-22] File Import Pipeline
Source: documentation/Architecture_FileImport.md

### Must-Have
- Remove STEP and PLY from the SDL_DialogFileFilter until their importers exist,
  or implement minimal parsers; selecting them currently produces a silent empty scene
- Move scene creation (ownedScenes.push_back / activeSceneIndex update) to after a
  successful Import() return; roll back on failure or unsupported format

### Should-Have
- Replace `new FileCallback` with `unique_ptr<FileCallback>::release()` + re-wrap inside
  the SDL lambda for RAII-safe cleanup
- Call `scene->MergeCoplanarFaces(solid)` in OBJImport and ThreeMFImport for consistency
  with STLImport
- Surface import errors to the user in the Files panel (e.g., brief error line under tab bar)

### Nice-to-Have
- Replace `std::map<dvec3, Point*, Vec3Compare>` with a spatial-hash deduplicator for
  large STL meshes (O(1) average vs O(log n))
- Add a basic PLY importer (binary + ASCII)
- Investigate a format-registry architecture for DoFileImport (Open/Closed extension)

---

## [2026-04-22] Camera
Source: documentation/Architecture_Camera.md

### Should-Have
- Make Camera members private; expose const accessors (GetOrthoSize, GetOrientation,
  GetTarget, GetAspectRatio); direct mutation currently bypasses cameraDirty
- Replace magic constants in Camera constructor with static constexpr members
  (DEFAULT_DISTANCE, DEFAULT_ORTHO_SIZE, DEPTH_RANGE)

### Nice-to-Have
- Move ScreenToWorld from Display into Camera (depends only on camera state; improves
  cohesion and testability)
- Change Display::GetCamera() to return `const Camera&` to avoid an unnecessary copy
- Add named-view presets (Top, Front, Right, Isometric)

---

## [2026-04-24] Settings (future expansion)
Source: discussion — persist more tuning knobs in `Settings` / `settings.xml`

### Appearance / color (high value)
- [ ] Expose UI depth luminance step (`Color::kStep`, currently `0.1f`) as a user setting
      (e.g. “UI contrast” or “depth step”); clamp to a safe range; wire Save/Load and UI
- [ ] Later: optional separate knobs for `kAccentLBoost`, scene greys (`kFaceL` / edge /
      point chain), `GetGrid()` / axis colours, flaw overlay alpha — only if product need

### Analysis (already parameterized in code, not in Settings)
- [ ] `ThinSection` / `SmallFeature` `heightToWidthRatio` (default `3.0`)
- [ ] `Stringing` `maxContourCount` (default `1`)

### Input / navigation
- [ ] `Input.hpp` gesture constants: `LOCK_FRAMES`, `ORBIT_RATIO_THRESHOLD`, `TOUCH_DEADZONE`
      (and related) as optional advanced settings if users want orbit/pan feel tuning

### Viewport / consistency
- [ ] Single source of truth for grid half-extent: `Settings::gridExtent` vs `Color::GRID_EXTENT`
      (avoid drift between the two)

### UI layout (lower priority)
- [ ] Optional “compact UI” / density: `UIGrid::CELL_SIZE`, `GAP`, panel radii / icon ratios,
      or fixed pixel gaps in `UIRenderer` — only if we want accessibility or power-user prefs

